## PART 3 — CORE SYSTEMS (with pseudocode)

### 3.1 The Hidden Deck
One standard 54-card deck (52 + 2 Jokers) is shared by both combatants for the encounter. Card type is derived purely from rank:

| Card type | Cards | Behavior | Value |
|---|---|---|---|
| Sorcery | 2–10 | Direct damage, then discard | rank-scaled |
| Status | Ace (×4) | Applies a status effect, **stays on field** as a visible marker until it expires | no direct damage |
| Creature | J / Q / K | Stays on field; owner chooses Attack or Block each turn | J=4, Q=5, K=6 |
| Wild | Joker (×2) | Cast-time choice: Sorcery (6 dmg, discard) or Creature (6 atk, stays on field) | 6 |

**Data-driven tip (Odin):** don't hand-write 54 card entries. Generate the deck procedurally at startup from two enums, and derive `CardType` from rank at generation time — this keeps balance changes to a couple of constants instead of 54 edits.

```odin
Suit :: enum { Clubs, Spades, Hearts, Diamonds }
CardType :: enum { Sorcery, Status, Creature, Wild }

Card :: struct {
    rank: int,      // 1=Ace, 2-10 numeric, 11=J, 12=Q, 13=K, 0=Joker
    suit: Suit,     // ignored for Jokers
    is_joker: bool,
    card_type: CardType,
}

derive_card_type :: proc(rank: int, is_joker: bool) -> CardType {
    if is_joker do return .Wild
    if rank == 1 do return .Status
    if rank >= 11 do return .Creature
    return .Sorcery
}

build_deck :: proc() -> [dynamic]Card {
    deck := make([dynamic]Card, 0, 54)
    for suit in Suit {
        for rank in 1..=13 {
            append(&deck, Card{rank, suit, false, derive_card_type(rank, false)})
        }
    }
    append(&deck, Card{0, .Clubs, true, .Wild}) // suit unused for jokers
    append(&deck, Card{0, .Clubs, true, .Wild})
    return deck
}
```

**Reshuffle rule:** once the shared deck is empty on any draw attempt, shuffle the discard pile into a fresh deck and continue. This should be one shared procedure called from every draw site (Channel draw, hand refill), never duplicated.

```odin
draw_card :: proc(state: ^EncounterState) -> Card {
    if len(state.deck) == 0 {
        reshuffle_discard_into_deck(state)
    }
    idx := len(state.deck) - 1
    card := state.deck[idx]
    pop(&state.deck)
    return card
}
```

### 3.2 Turn Structure Overview
Every turn, for both player and enemy, in this fixed order:

1. **Creature stance resolution** (existing field creatures act on their assigned stance from last turn — Attack or Block)
2. **Channel phase** (attempt to gain mana)
3. **Draw step** (optional mulligan)
4. **Cast phase** (spend mana on a hand card; assign new stances to any freshly summoned or existing creatures for *next* turn)

**Pseudocode — full turn:**
```odin
run_turn :: proc(state: ^EncounterState, acting: ^Combatant, opposing: ^Combatant) {
    resolve_creature_stances(acting, opposing)       // step 1
    channel_phase(state, acting)                     // step 2
    draw_step(state, acting)                          // step 3
    cast_phase(state, acting, opposing)               // step 4
}
```

### 3.3 Channel Phase (mana generation — replaces MTG's land drop)
```odin
channel_phase :: proc(state: ^EncounterState, c: ^Combatant) {
    if roll_d20() + c.attrs.resolve_bonus >= 11 {
        card := draw_card(state)
        c.mana_pool[card.suit] += card.rank
        return
    }
    // second attempt
    if roll_d20() + c.attrs.resolve_bonus >= 11 {
        card := draw_card(state)
        c.mana_pool[card.suit] += card.rank
        return
    }
    // blood magic fallback — never fully stalls
    c.hp -= 2
    wild_token := draw_card(state) // identity never revealed to either player
    c.wild_mana += 1 // flat 1 mana, any suit, spent as chosen at cast time
    move_to_discard_facedown(state, wild_token)
}
```
**Tip:** keep `wild_mana` as a separate int on `Combatant`, not folded into `mana_pool[Suit]`, since it can satisfy *any* suit — resolve it as a fallback check in `can_afford()` rather than trying to force it into the suit-indexed array.

### 3.4 Draw Step (semi-mulligan)
```odin
draw_step :: proc(state: ^EncounterState, c: ^Combatant, mulligan_mask: []bool) {
    for i, discard in mulligan_mask {
        if discard {
            move_to_discard(state, c.hand[i])
            c.hand[i] = draw_card(state)
        }
    }
}
```
For the player, `mulligan_mask` comes from UI input (toggle which hand slots to redraw). For enemies, generate it from AI logic (see §3.8).

### 3.5 Cast Phase
```odin
can_afford :: proc(c: ^Combatant, card: Card) -> bool {
    return c.mana_pool[card.suit] >= card.rank || c.wild_mana > 0
}

cast_card :: proc(state: ^EncounterState, caster: ^Combatant, target: ^Combatant, card: Card) {
    spend_mana(caster, card)

    switch card.card_type {
    case .Sorcery:
        tier := run_timing_minigame(caster.attrs.focus_bonus)
        dmg := roll_d6() + rank_to_damage_bonus(card.rank) + caster.attrs.arcana_bonus
        dmg = apply_crit_bonus(dmg, tier)
        deal_damage(target, dmg)
        move_to_discard(state, card)

    case .Status:
        tier := run_timing_minigame(caster.attrs.focus_bonus)
        if tier == .Clean || tier == .Perfect {
            apply_status_marker(target, suit_to_status(card.suit), duration = 3)
        }
        add_field_status(caster, card, target) // stays visible on field until expired

    case .Creature:
        add_field_creature(caster, card) // no timing check on summon itself

    case .Wild:
        mode := decide_wild_mode(caster) // player choice via UI, or AI heuristic
        if mode == .Sorcery {
            tier := run_timing_minigame(caster.attrs.focus_bonus)
            dmg := roll_d6() + 6 + caster.attrs.arcana_bonus
            dmg = apply_crit_bonus(dmg, tier)
            deal_damage(target, dmg)
            move_to_discard(state, card)
        } else {
            add_field_creature(caster, card)
        }
    }
}
```

### 3.6 Creature Field & Combat
```odin
FieldCreature :: struct {
    rank: int,           // 11/12/13, Joker-as-creature treated as 13
    attack_value: int,   // 4/5/6
    stance: Stance,      // Attack or Block, chosen at end of caster's cast phase for NEXT turn
}

resolve_creature_stances :: proc(acting: ^Combatant, opposing: ^Combatant) {
    for creature in acting.field_creatures {
        if creature.stance == .Attack {
            blocker := find_blocker(opposing)
            if blocker != nil {
                resolve_creature_trade(creature, blocker, acting, opposing)
            } else {
                deal_damage(opposing, creature.attack_value)
            }
        }
        // .Block creatures do nothing offensively this turn, but remain available to intercept
    }
}

resolve_creature_trade :: proc(attacker: ^FieldCreature, blocker: ^FieldCreature, atk_owner, blk_owner: ^Combatant) {
    if attacker.rank > blocker.rank {
        remove_creature(blk_owner, blocker)
    } else if blocker.rank > attacker.rank {
        remove_creature(atk_owner, attacker)
    } else {
        remove_creature(atk_owner, attacker)
        remove_creature(blk_owner, blocker)
    }
    // removed creatures go to discard pile, re-enter the deck on next reshuffle
}
```
**Field slot cap:** enforce a constant (`MAX_FIELD_CREATURES :: 2`) when adding a creature; if full, either reject the cast (simplest) or replace the oldest (`ordered_remove` from the dynamic array at index 0 before appending).

### 3.7 Timing Minigame (crit/status determination — reused everywhere)
```odin
TimingTier :: enum { Miss, Weak, Clean, Perfect }

run_timing_minigame :: proc(zone_width_bonus: f32) -> TimingTier {
    // Called once per player input frame-loop while the marker sweeps;
    // this pseudocode shows the *resolution* step once the player presses the stop key.
    zone_width := BASE_ZONE_WIDTH + zone_width_bonus
    dist := abs(marker_position - zone_center)
    if dist < zone_width * 0.15 do return .Perfect
    if dist < zone_width * 0.5  do return .Clean
    if dist < zone_width * 1.0  do return .Weak
    return .Miss
}
```
**Odin/Raylib tip:** drive `marker_position` from `rl.GetFrameTime()` accumulation, not frame count, so the minigame feels identical regardless of the Chromebook's actual framerate. Something like:
```odin
marker_position += marker_speed * rl.GetFrameTime()
if marker_position > BAR_WIDTH || marker_position < 0 {
    marker_speed = -marker_speed // bounce
}
```

### 3.8 Enemy AI (no human input — flat heuristics only)
```odin
AIBehavior :: enum { Aggressive, Defensive, Random }

choose_enemy_cast :: proc(enemy: ^Combatant, behavior: AIBehavior) -> Maybe(Card) {
    affordable := affordable_cards_in_hand(enemy)
    if len(affordable) == 0 do return nil

    switch behavior {
    case .Aggressive:
        return highest_rank(affordable)
    case .Defensive:
        hearts := filter_by_suit(affordable, .Hearts)
        return len(hearts) > 0 ? hearts[0] : highest_rank(affordable)
    case .Random:
        return affordable[rand.int_max(len(affordable))]
    }
}

choose_enemy_stance :: proc(behavior: AIBehavior, has_board_advantage: bool) -> Stance {
    switch behavior {
    case .Aggressive: return .Attack
    case .Defensive:  return has_board_advantage ? .Attack : .Block
    case .Random:      return rand.int_max(2) == 0 ? .Attack : .Block
    }
}
```
No behavior tree, no utility scoring — a single switch per decision point is enough for jam scope and is trivial to balance by eye.

### 3.9 Status Effects
Keep this to 4 effects max (one per hidden suit) so it's buildable in a day:
```odin
StatusKind :: enum { Burn, Freeze, Ward, Drain }

suit_to_status :: proc(s: Suit) -> StatusKind {
    switch s {
    case .Clubs:    return .Burn    // damage over time
    case .Spades:   return .Freeze  // skip next action
    case .Hearts:   return .Ward    // reduce next incoming hit
    case .Diamonds: return .Drain   // steal HP to caster
    }
}

tick_status_effects :: proc(c: ^Combatant) {
    for &status in c.field_statuses {
        switch status.kind {
        case .Burn:  deal_damage(c, BURN_TICK_DAMAGE)
        case .Freeze: c.skip_next_action = true
        case .Ward:  // consumed reactively on next incoming hit, not ticked here
        case .Drain: // one-time effect at application, not ticked
        }
        status.turns_remaining -= 1
    }
    remove_expired_statuses(c) // moves expired FieldStatus entries to discard
}
```

