## PART 8 — DAY-BY-DAY BUILD PLAN (6 days)

**Day 0 (pre-jam):** Validate Odin + Raylib actually builds and runs on the Chromebook (Crostini). This is the single biggest technical risk given prior LLVM instability — test this before writing game logic. Fallback: build on any available Windows machine if Crostini proves unreliable.

**Day 1:** Screen state machine (`GameScreen` enum + switch). Deck generation + shuffle + draw/reshuffle. Render a placeholder battle screen: HP bars, empty spell menu box. Build the `Tween` helper and lock the color palette.

**Day 2:** Channel phase (d20, mana pool, blood-magic fallback) wired to real UI (MP-style counters per flavor-named school). Draw step / mulligan UI. Cast phase for Sorcery only (no timing minigame yet — flat damage) to prove the resource loop end-to-end.

**Day 3:** Timing minigame + crit tiers + d6 damage + status application (Burn/Freeze/Ward/Drain, capped at these 4). Hit flash, cast lunge, floating damage numbers via Tween.

**Day 4:** Creature system — field slots, Attack/Block stance UI, trade resolution. Enemy AI (3 behavior tags). Equipment + attribute leveling (Shop/Bonfire merged screen if time-pressed). Data tables for enemies/gear/node sequence.

**Day 5:** Tutorial encounter (forced hand, prompt state machine). Full node sequence wired end-to-end, including the Boss (suit/rank immunity rule, phase-2 stat bump). Playtest a full run start to finish.

**Day 6:** Buffer day. Balance pass using the data tables only (no logic changes). Cut anything broken rather than fixing late. Write flavor text for remaining gear/enemies. Package build, write the jam page, submit early.

